                <br /><br />                               
                <p>The culinary masters behind the landmark INC Restaurant in New Brunswick and Warren&rsquo;s own Uproot are bringing a taste of Latin America to Somerville this fall. A late September opening is planned for Salted Lime Bar &amp; Kitchen, a Modern Latin-themed eatery preparing to open its doors at 46 East Main Street &ndash; and area foodies can&rsquo;t wait!</p>
                <p>&ldquo;Everyone is incredibly excited,&rdquo; says Danny McGill, Operations Manager of Mark Daniel Hospitality and Salted Lime&rsquo;s General Manager. &ldquo;The city of Somerville has been terrific. We were part of this year&rsquo;s Taste of Somerville, as well as the Girls Night Out, and the reception was amazing.&rdquo;</p>
                <table align="right">
